CSE
ID

=============================
Automatic Players - Strategies
=============================

WhateverPlayer:
  Randomly selects an empty cell on the board each turn.

NaivePlayer:
  Scans the board row by row, left to right, and places its mark on the
  first empty cell found.

SmartPlayer:
  Uses the minimax algorithm with a depth limit to evaluate future game
  states and select the move that maximizes its chance of winning.

=============================
Design Decisions
=============================

Each player class (WhateverPlayer, NaivePlayer, SmartPlayer, HumanPlayer)
implements the Player interface, which exposes a single method: playTurn.
This design follows the Open/Closed Principle from OOP - the Tournament
and Game classes depend only on the Player interface, so new player types
can be added without modifying any existing code.

Similarly, Renderer is an interface implemented by ConsoleRenderer and
VoidRenderer, decoupling the rendering logic from the game logic.

The PlayerFactory and RendererFactory classes centralize instantiation,
keeping the Tournament.main method clean and extensible.

